1
00:00:33,082 --> 00:00:34,200
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

2
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:36,835
♪ NOW AND THEN I GET BENT ♪

3
00:00:36,903 --> 00:00:40,039
♪ FROM ALL THE THINGS
I CANNOT CHANGE ♪

4
00:00:40,106 --> 00:00:41,840
♪
♪ IT'S JUST MY CIRCUMSTANCE

5
00:00:41,908 --> 00:00:44,577
♪ AND IN MY HEAD, I AM DEAD ♪

6
00:00:44,643 --> 00:00:47,313
♪ WHEN DEEP INSIDE
I FEEL NO PAIN ♪

7
00:00:47,346 --> 00:00:48,514
HEY, JERK!

8
00:00:48,581 --> 00:00:51,717
♪
♪ I'M HANGING BY A THREAD

9
00:00:51,817 --> 00:00:56,155
♪♪ TORN INSIDE MY MIND ♪

10
00:00:56,221 --> 00:00:59,925
♪ SO I'M TURNING
TO THE OTHER SIDE ♪

11
00:00:59,992 --> 00:01:04,730
♪ I HEAR YOU CALL ME ♪

12
00:01:04,830 --> 00:01:10,536
♪ IN MY DREAM
YOU'RE RIGHT BESIDE ME ♪

13
00:01:12,939 --> 00:01:18,010
♪ TAKE AWAY MY LIFE ♪

14
00:01:18,093 --> 00:01:23,032
♪ I HEAR YOU CALL ME ♪

15
00:01:23,099 --> 00:01:28,270
♪ IN MY DREAM
YOU'RE RIGHT BESIDE ME ♪

16
00:01:28,337 --> 00:01:33,475
♪ I KNOW THAT I'LL DO ♪♪

17
00:01:33,576 --> 00:01:40,816
♪ ANYTHING YOU ASK
I'LL DO FOR YOU ♪

18
00:01:40,916 --> 00:01:43,436
♪ FOR YOU ♪

19
00:01:43,502 --> 00:01:46,071
♪♪ FOR YOU ♪

20
00:01:51,060 --> 00:01:53,329
HEY, COACH WANTS US TO BE
UP THE RINK EARLY TONIGHT,

21
00:01:53,362 --> 00:01:55,064
SO WE CAN WARM UP
FOR THE GAME.

22
00:01:55,131 --> 00:01:56,832
LIKE I NEED IT.

23
00:02:02,938 --> 00:02:05,508
ANTICIPATE THE BALL.

24
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:20,206
[ GASPS ]

25
00:02:20,273 --> 00:02:22,175
[ LAUGHS ]
DUDE, SHE TOTALLY BIFFED IT.

26
00:02:23,842 --> 00:02:25,278
KEEP WALKING, GUYS.

27
00:02:26,945 --> 00:02:28,448
YOU TOO, COLTON.

28
00:02:44,196 --> 00:02:45,564
ARE YOU OKAY?

29
00:02:45,631 --> 00:02:47,400
YEAH.

30
00:03:01,114 --> 00:03:02,681
NICE SERVE.

31
00:03:02,748 --> 00:03:06,052
YOU TRYING TO SHOW ME UP?
NICE HIT.

32
00:03:07,286 --> 00:03:09,588
NOW IF ONLY YOU COULD DO THAT
EVERY TIME.

33
00:03:11,074 --> 00:03:13,242
[ WHISTLES ]
LET'S BRING IT IN!

34
00:03:13,309 --> 00:03:15,961
LET'S GO, LET'S GO.
HUSTLE.

35
00:03:16,028 --> 00:03:18,531
YOU'RE DOING
SO MUCH BETTER.

36
00:03:18,598 --> 00:03:20,600
YEAH, BUT I COULDN'T GET
MY BACKHAND.

37
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:24,403
SORRY ABOUT MY BROTHER.

38
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:27,073
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.
IT'S COLTON'S.

39
00:03:27,139 --> 00:03:28,574
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN UP.

40
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:31,010
A LOT OF YOU HAVE HEARD ABOUT
THE CLAIRVILLE TENNIS PROGRAM.

41
00:03:31,077 --> 00:03:33,946
IT'S AN INVITATION-ONLY CAMP
HELD OVER THE SUMMER,

42
00:03:34,013 --> 00:03:35,347
AND THOSE THAT ARE CHOSEN

43
00:03:35,447 --> 00:03:37,316
WILL BE PLAYING WITH THE VER
Y BEST OF PLAYERS --

44
00:03:37,349 --> 00:03:38,617
EVEN PROS.

45
00:03:38,684 --> 00:03:41,153
NOW, I CALLED IN A FAVOR
AND CONVINCED THEM

46
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:43,022
TO COME SEE YOU AT THE END
OF THE SEASON.

47
00:03:43,089 --> 00:03:46,425
NOW, IT'S GONNA REQUIRE A LOT
OF HARD WORK AND DEDICATION,

48
00:03:46,492 --> 00:03:48,995
AND I THINK YOU'RE ALL
GREAT PLAYERS.

49
00:03:49,061 --> 00:03:51,063
I THINK YOU ALL HAVE A CHANCE
OF BEING CHOSEN,

50
00:03:51,130 --> 00:03:53,132
BUT NOT WITHOUT PRACTICE.

51
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:55,668
SO LET'S GET BACK TO IT.
LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

52
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,743
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

53
00:04:05,778 --> 00:04:07,914
COLTON, WE WERE WORRIED
ABOUT YOU.

54
00:04:07,980 --> 00:04:10,717
COME, SIT DOWN.
WE'VE ALREADY BLESSED THE FOOD.

55
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,988
WE GOT YOUR QUARTER'S
REPORT CARD.

56
00:04:16,055 --> 00:04:17,256
SO?
HEY!

57
00:04:17,323 --> 00:04:19,058
SHOW A LITTLE RESPECT,
COLTON.

58
00:04:19,091 --> 00:04:20,392
WHAT ABOUT COLLEGE?

59
00:04:20,459 --> 00:04:21,861
IF YOU DON'T GET
YOUR GRADES UP,

60
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,730
NO UNIVERSITY
WILL ACCEPT YOU.

61
00:04:23,796 --> 00:04:25,097
CAN I STAY OUT
TILL 11:00 TONIGHT?

62
00:04:25,197 --> 00:04:26,365
I'M GOING
TO THE HOCKEY GAME.

63
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:27,399
GREAT.

64
00:04:27,466 --> 00:04:28,400
HEY, WE'LL GO, TOO.

65
00:04:28,467 --> 00:04:29,802
NO, YOU WON'T!

66
00:04:29,869 --> 00:04:31,270
COLTON, WE WANT
TO WATCH YOU PLAY.

67
00:04:31,337 --> 00:04:32,805
I DON'T CARE.

68
00:04:32,872 --> 00:04:34,874
Ashley: IT'S THE LAST GAME
OF THE SEASON.

69
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,009
I'M GOING, AND IT'S NOT
BECAUSE OF YOU.

70
00:04:37,076 --> 00:04:39,211
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME
SINCE YOU'VE LET US, SO --

71
00:04:39,278 --> 00:04:41,848
SO, WHY START AGAIN NOW?!

72
00:04:41,914 --> 00:04:43,783
[ SIGHS ]

73
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:45,251
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

74
00:04:45,317 --> 00:04:46,719
TO THE GAME!

75
00:04:48,554 --> 00:04:51,457
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

76
00:04:51,523 --> 00:04:55,127
[ THE PLANET SMASHERS'
"SHE'S LATE" PLAYS ]

77
00:04:55,194 --> 00:04:57,980
Man: WELCOME TO THE FINAL
ELIMINATION GAME...

78
00:05:10,593 --> 00:05:11,911
SARA!

79
00:05:13,946 --> 00:05:15,447
SO, HOW WAS PRACTICE?

80
00:05:15,514 --> 00:05:16,648
ASK LIZ.

81
00:05:16,716 --> 00:05:17,917
HEY, I DID WELL.

82
00:05:19,886 --> 00:05:22,354
Man: AND THE BLUE DEVILS
STEAL THE WIN!

83
00:05:22,421 --> 00:05:24,156
I'M SO EXCITED
FOR THE CLAIRVILLE CAMP,

84
00:05:24,223 --> 00:05:25,291
BUT I DOUBT I'LL MAKE IT.

85
00:05:25,357 --> 00:05:26,726
DON'T SAY THAT.

86
00:05:26,793 --> 00:05:29,461
EVERYBODY KNOWS THEY USUALLY
CHOOSE THE JUNIORS OR SENIORS,

87
00:05:29,528 --> 00:05:30,863
AND I'M JUST A SOPHOMORE.

88
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:32,799
HEY, YOU NEVER KNOW.

89
00:05:37,669 --> 00:05:39,788
[ BUZZER ]

90
00:05:39,855 --> 00:05:41,356
Man: HE SHOOTS...

91
00:05:41,423 --> 00:05:44,059
NO GOOD!

92
00:05:46,261 --> 00:05:47,713
SEEMS LIKE NO MATTER
WHAT THEY DO,

93
00:05:47,780 --> 00:05:50,249
THE MAPLE LEAFS AREN'T GONNA
CATCH A BREAK.

94
00:05:50,316 --> 00:05:52,551
YOUR BROTHER IS SO HOT.

95
00:05:52,618 --> 00:05:54,653
IF YOU THINK SO, LIZ.

96
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:57,756
IF ONLY THE THOUGHT OF HIM
DIDN'T MAKE ME GAG.

97
00:05:57,823 --> 00:05:59,792
SORRY.
I DIDN'T REALLY MEAN THAT.

98
00:05:59,858 --> 00:06:01,727
IT'S OKAY.
I UNDERSTAND.

99
00:06:01,794 --> 00:06:04,430
REMEMBER, I LIVE WITH HIM.

100
00:06:09,835 --> 00:06:11,186
Crowd: OHH!

101
00:06:16,291 --> 00:06:18,227
Man: AND THAT'S THE END
OF A LOSING SEASON

102
00:06:18,293 --> 00:06:19,895
FOR THE MAPLE LEAFS.

103
00:06:25,868 --> 00:06:28,603
HEY, COLTON.
THAT WAS A GOOD GAME TONIGHT.

104
00:06:28,671 --> 00:06:31,040
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN IF ANYONE
ELSE HAD BEEN PLAYING.

105
00:06:31,106 --> 00:06:32,374
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

106
00:06:32,441 --> 00:06:34,276
YEAH, IF THE GOALIE WOULD HAVE
DONE HIS JOB,

107
00:06:34,343 --> 00:06:36,211
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE ANYTHING
TO COMPLAIN ABOUT.

108
00:06:36,278 --> 00:06:37,596
THAT'S RIGHT.

109
00:06:37,663 --> 00:06:39,098
Girl: HEY, JOHN.

110
00:06:39,165 --> 00:06:41,300
IT HAD TO BE THE LAST GAME
FOR US, TOO.

111
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:42,601
TOTALLY THEIR FAULT.

112
00:06:42,668 --> 00:06:43,969
[ LAUGHS ]

113
00:06:44,035 --> 00:06:46,405
EDDIE,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

114
00:06:46,472 --> 00:06:48,774
OH, HE'S JUST HANGING OUT
WITH US.

115
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,459
ANYTHING WRONG WITH THAT?

116
00:06:52,527 --> 00:06:54,029
OH, SARA, BY THE WAY,

117
00:06:54,096 --> 00:06:56,232
THAT WAS SOME PRETTY FANCY
FOOTWORK YOU WERE DOING.

118
00:06:56,299 --> 00:06:57,900
ALWAYS SPEND THAT MUCH TIME
ON YOUR BUTT?

119
00:06:57,966 --> 00:06:59,535
[ LAUGHTER ]

120
00:06:59,602 --> 00:07:01,036
NOT AS MUCH TIME
AS YOU DID TONIGHT.

121
00:07:01,103 --> 00:07:02,371
OHH.
OHH. OHH.

122
00:07:02,438 --> 00:07:03,572
WHY DON'T YOU GET LOST,
NARK?

123
00:07:03,639 --> 00:07:05,574
COME ON, SARA.

124
00:07:05,641 --> 00:07:07,944
B-B-B-BYE!

125
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:09,979
[ LAUGHS ]

126
00:07:21,523 --> 00:07:24,826
GOOD MORNING.
WHAT ARE YOU COOKING?

127
00:07:24,894 --> 00:07:26,062
OMELET.

128
00:07:26,128 --> 00:07:29,598
WE HAVE GREEN PEPPERS, TOMATOES,
CHEESE, MUSHROOMS,

129
00:07:29,665 --> 00:07:31,067
AND THEN A LITTLE SALSA
TO TOP IT OFF.

130
00:07:31,133 --> 00:07:32,668
WELL, THAT LOOKS
REALLY GOOD.

131
00:07:32,734 --> 00:07:33,835
HOW WAS WORK?

132
00:07:33,903 --> 00:07:35,104
OH, LONG.

133
00:07:35,171 --> 00:07:37,506
PARTY OF 10 CAME INTO
THE RESTAURANT FOR DINNER,

134
00:07:37,573 --> 00:07:39,275
THEN ONE OF THEM GOT SICK
ON VEAL,

135
00:07:39,341 --> 00:07:41,343
AND THAT TRIGGERED IT
FOR EVERYBODY ELSE, AND --

136
00:07:41,410 --> 00:07:43,645
WELL, LET'S JUST SAY
IT WASN'T PRETTY.

137
00:07:43,712 --> 00:07:45,514
WELL, ON THAT NOTE...

138
00:07:45,581 --> 00:07:47,083
THANKS.

139
00:07:47,149 --> 00:07:49,919
THAT LOOKS GREAT.
HOW WAS PRACTICE YESTERDAY?

140
00:07:49,986 --> 00:07:52,654
SAME AS USUAL.

141
00:07:52,721 --> 00:07:55,124
WHAT?

142
00:07:55,191 --> 00:07:57,159
IS COACH GIVING YOU
A HARD TIME?

143
00:07:57,226 --> 00:08:00,997
WHAT? NO, I MEAN, I GUESS
I SHOULD BE EXCITED.

144
00:08:01,063 --> 00:08:03,599
HE SAID SOME CLAIRVILLE PEOPLE
ARE COMING TO OUR SCHOOL.

145
00:08:03,665 --> 00:08:04,866
REALLY?

146
00:08:04,934 --> 00:08:07,669
YEAH. AND HE THINKS I HAVE
A REALLY GREAT SHOT

147
00:08:07,736 --> 00:08:08,804
OF GETTING INVITED.

148
00:08:08,870 --> 00:08:09,871
WELL, HE'S RIGHT.

149
00:08:09,939 --> 00:08:11,107
MOM.

150
00:08:11,173 --> 00:08:14,110
SARA, YOU'RE ONE OF THE BEST
PLAYERS ON THE TEAM.

151
00:08:14,176 --> 00:08:16,245
WELL, THAT'S TILL I HAVE TO PLAY
IN FRONT OF EVERYBODY

152
00:08:16,312 --> 00:08:17,396
AND GET NERVOUS AND MESS UP.

153
00:08:17,463 --> 00:08:19,031
DON'T PSYCHE YOURSELF OUT.

154
00:08:19,098 --> 00:08:20,532
TOO LATE.

155
00:08:24,470 --> 00:08:26,705
FINALLY.
WHATEVER.

156
00:08:26,772 --> 00:08:28,640
YOU'RE TWO HOURS LATE.
MIKE WOULD BE TICKED,

157
00:08:28,707 --> 00:08:30,876
AND I HAVEN'T HAD A BR
EAK SINCE MY SHIFT STARTED.

158
00:08:30,942 --> 00:08:32,411
WELL, YOU'RE STILL ALIVE.

159
00:08:32,478 --> 00:08:33,612
COVER MY REGISTER.

160
00:08:34,730 --> 00:08:37,633
NO WAY. THIS GUY'S
GONNA PROBABLY ORDER
TWO OF EVERYTHING.

161
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:39,768
I COVERED FOR YOU BEING LATE.
IT'S YOUR TURN.

162
00:08:39,835 --> 00:08:41,369
AND BE NICE.

163
00:08:45,407 --> 00:08:48,811
I WANT TWO EXTRA-LARGE POPCORNS
AND DRINKS,

164
00:08:48,877 --> 00:08:50,713
AND DO YOU SUPERSIZE?

165
00:08:50,779 --> 00:08:52,631
NO.

166
00:08:55,533 --> 00:08:57,803
THAT'LL BE $11.50.

167
00:09:04,509 --> 00:09:06,378
Girl: HEY, WHAT'S UP?

168
00:09:06,444 --> 00:09:07,947
NO, I'M WORKING.

169
00:09:09,381 --> 00:09:11,683
YEAH, ARE WE STILL ON
FOR TONIGHT?

170
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:14,019
YEAH, I'LL CALL YOU.

171
00:09:14,086 --> 00:09:15,220
OKAY, BYE.

172
00:09:15,287 --> 00:09:16,621
[ TELEPHONE BEEPS ]

173
00:09:16,705 --> 00:09:18,006
OKAY, I'M BACK.

174
00:09:18,073 --> 00:09:20,092
OH, I'M GLAD.
THANKS.

175
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:21,077
COLTON.

176
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:22,878
BLAKE, GUYS.
WHAT'S UP?

177
00:09:22,945 --> 00:09:24,146
WHEN DO YOU GET OFF WORK?

178
00:09:24,212 --> 00:09:26,415
YEAH, DUDE,
WE ARE SO BORED.

179
00:09:26,482 --> 00:09:28,316
I CAN THINK OF SOMETHING
TO FIX THAT.

180
00:09:28,384 --> 00:09:29,317
WHERE'S EDDIE?

181
00:09:29,418 --> 00:09:31,153
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
GOT TO RUN.

182
00:09:31,219 --> 00:09:32,187
YOU JUST GOT HERE.

183
00:09:32,254 --> 00:09:33,639
WELL, THAT'S TOO BAD.

184
00:09:33,706 --> 00:09:35,841
LET'S GO, GUYS.

185
00:09:39,878 --> 00:09:41,980
[ SPRAY-PAINT CANS RATTLING ]

186
00:09:44,382 --> 00:09:46,885
YOU HANG OUT WITH US,
YOU DO WHAT WE DO.

187
00:09:46,952 --> 00:09:47,986
Blake: READY, BRO?

188
00:09:48,053 --> 00:09:51,140
John:
LET'S DO THIS THING.

189
00:10:04,419 --> 00:10:05,920
HEY!

190
00:10:05,987 --> 00:10:07,656
DUDE!

191
00:10:07,722 --> 00:10:11,193
YEAH, SOMEONE JUST VANDALIZED
THE CHURCH.

192
00:10:15,464 --> 00:10:17,132
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

193
00:10:20,902 --> 00:10:23,305
STAY DOWN.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THIS.

194
00:10:23,372 --> 00:10:27,342
WHO'S OUT HERE?
I CALLED THE POLICE.

195
00:10:27,409 --> 00:10:30,712
THE BEST THING FOR YOU
IS JUST GIVE YOURSELVES UP.

196
00:10:30,779 --> 00:10:32,147
JUST HELP CLEAN UP THE MESS.

197
00:10:32,214 --> 00:10:35,417
I DON'T THINK YOU'LL GET
IN TOO MUCH TROUBLE.

198
00:10:35,484 --> 00:10:38,387
[ GRUNTING ]

199
00:10:38,453 --> 00:10:40,455
COME ON, DUDE.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

200
00:10:45,059 --> 00:10:46,861
YOU KNOW WHAT TIME COLTON
CAME HOME?

201
00:10:46,928 --> 00:10:49,164
HE WASN'T HERE LAST NIGHT
AT MIDNIGHT WHEN I CHECKED,

202
00:10:49,231 --> 00:10:50,265
BUT HE'S HERE NOW.

203
00:10:50,332 --> 00:10:52,434
3:43 A.M.
WHAT?

204
00:10:52,501 --> 00:10:53,868
HE GOT HOME AT 3:43
IN THE MORNING.

205
00:10:53,936 --> 00:10:55,938
HE WOKE ME UP WHEN HE HIT
HIS FOOT AGAINST HIS WEIGHTS.

206
00:10:56,005 --> 00:10:57,940
THAT'S TWO NIGHTS IN A ROW
PAST MIDNIGHT.

207
00:10:58,007 --> 00:11:00,342
I CAN'T WAIT TILLMYCURFEW
DOESN'T EXIST.

208
00:11:00,375 --> 00:11:01,443
COLTONHASA CURFEW.

209
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:03,312
HE JUST CHOOSES NOT
TO FOLLOW IT,

210
00:11:03,378 --> 00:11:05,280
AND HEWILLSUFFER
THE CONSEQUENCES.

211
00:11:05,397 --> 00:11:07,165
EXCELLENT.

212
00:11:07,232 --> 00:11:09,501
I GOT TO SEE IF ANYBODY'S
HAD ANY BETTER LUCK

213
00:11:09,568 --> 00:11:11,403
CLEANING THAT STUFF
OFF THE CHURCH.

214
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:13,238
WHAT STUFF OFF THE CHURCH?

215
00:11:13,304 --> 00:11:14,906
SOMEONE GRAFFITIED
THE CHURCH LAST NIGHT.

216
00:11:14,973 --> 00:11:16,408
WHO?
I DON'T KNOW.

217
00:11:16,475 --> 00:11:19,545
.
MR. COOPER SAW FOUR OF THEM,
AND ONE OF THEM ATTACKED HIM

218
00:11:19,611 --> 00:11:21,680
IS HE ALL RIGHT?
I'M SURE HE'LL BE FINE,

219
00:11:21,747 --> 00:11:23,181
BUT WHAT I DON'T
UNDERSTAND IS

220
00:11:23,248 --> 00:11:25,300
WHY WOULD SOMEONE DO SOMETHING
LIKE THAT?

221
00:11:29,304 --> 00:11:30,672
WHAT?!

222
00:11:30,738 --> 00:11:33,375
CHURCH STARTS IN 10 MINUTES.
ARE YOU GOING?

223
00:11:33,441 --> 00:11:34,476
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

224
00:11:34,542 --> 00:11:35,811
I JUST THOUGHT I'D ASK.

225
00:11:35,878 --> 00:11:37,045
WELL, DON'T.

226
00:11:37,112 --> 00:11:38,246
FINE!

227
00:12:17,869 --> 00:12:19,270
SO, WE'RE PLAYING
VOLLEYBALL

228
00:12:19,337 --> 00:12:20,739
AT OUR NEXT WEEK'S
YOUTH ACTIVITY.

229
00:12:20,806 --> 00:12:21,973
OH, YEAH.

230
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,842
OH, MY AIM IS
TERRIBLE.

231
00:12:23,875 --> 00:12:26,144
AMAZING, SINCE IN TENNIS,
IT'S DEADLY.

232
00:12:26,211 --> 00:12:28,880
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE THAT
YOU CAN BE SO GOOD AT ONE SPORT

233
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:31,216
AND MISERABLE AT ANOTHER
RELATED SPORT?

234
00:12:31,282 --> 00:12:33,902
IT'S NOT RELATED.
IT'SCOMPLETELYDIFFERENT.

235
00:12:33,969 --> 00:12:35,737
KEEP TELLING YOURSELF THAT.

236
00:12:35,803 --> 00:12:37,372
MR. NIXON SAID
WE SHOULD BRING OTHERS,

237
00:12:37,439 --> 00:12:39,474
ESPECIALLY THOSE WHO HAVEN'T
BEEN AT CHURCH LATELY.

238
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:40,793
THERE'S ALWAYS
COLTON PRATT.

239
00:12:40,860 --> 00:12:43,328
DON'T EVEN JOKE ABOUT THAT.

240
00:12:43,395 --> 00:12:44,997
IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

241
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:46,731
WHAT?

242
00:12:46,832 --> 00:12:48,100
YOU DON'T KNOW?

243
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:49,501
WELL, I KNOW HE'S A JERK.

244
00:12:49,568 --> 00:12:50,735
YOU HAVE TO HEAR THIS.

245
00:12:50,836 --> 00:12:52,838
MNH-MNH.
DO WE HAVE TO RELIVE THIS?

246
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:54,373
NO, JUST YOU.

247
00:12:54,439 --> 00:12:56,175
SO, LAST YEAR, THERE WAS
THIS STATUE OF CHRIST

248
00:12:56,242 --> 00:12:57,609
.
OUTSIDE THE CHURCH

249
00:12:57,676 --> 00:13:00,279
IT'S NOT THERE ANYMORE BECAUSE
SOMEONE BROKE IT ON PURPOSE,

250
00:13:00,346 --> 00:13:01,747
AND SARA KNEW WHO.

251
00:13:01,813 --> 00:13:04,450
SHE TOLD MR. COOPER, AND COLTON
WAS CHARGED WITH VANDALISM.

252
00:13:04,516 --> 00:13:07,286
HE GOT, LIKE, 200 HOURS
OF COMMUNITY SERVICE.

253
00:13:07,353 --> 00:13:10,121
HE WAS SO TICKED OFF AFTER THAT
HE HASN'T COME TO CHURCH SINCE,

254
00:13:10,222 --> 00:13:12,107
NOT LIKE ANYBODY
WANTS HIM THERE ANYMORE.

255
00:13:12,174 --> 00:13:14,843
THANK YOU, LIZ.
LET'S MOVE ON.

256
00:13:14,910 --> 00:13:16,411
WOW.

257
00:13:16,478 --> 00:13:18,413
EVER SINCE THEN,
HE'S BEEN WORSE.

258
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:20,615
HE'S MEAN, AND, WELL,
YOU'VE SEEN IT.

259
00:13:20,682 --> 00:13:22,517
WELL, WHAT ABOUT EDDIE?

260
00:13:22,584 --> 00:13:23,718
I DON'T THINK SO.

261
00:13:23,785 --> 00:13:26,788
HE'S BEEN HANGING OUT
WITH COLTON A LOT LATELY.

262
00:13:26,855 --> 00:13:29,208
MAYBE HE JUST NEEDS
BETTER FRIENDS.

263
00:13:29,275 --> 00:13:30,642
HE USED TO HANG OUT
WITH US,

264
00:13:30,742 --> 00:13:33,128
BUT NOW HE THINKS
COLTON'S SO "COOL."

265
00:13:33,195 --> 00:13:34,830
WELL, EDDIE LIVES DOWN
THE STREET FROM ME.

266
00:13:34,897 --> 00:13:35,831
I'LL INVITE HIM.

267
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:37,065
GOOD LUCK.

268
00:13:40,085 --> 00:13:41,553
Colton: HEY,
YOU GOT THE HOMEWORK?

269
00:13:41,620 --> 00:13:44,222
OH, YEAH. HERE.

270
00:13:44,289 --> 00:13:45,957
COME ON, EDDIE.

271
00:13:52,548 --> 00:13:54,382
HEY, EDDIE.
WHAT'S UP?

272
00:13:54,482 --> 00:13:56,985
UH, HEY.

273
00:13:57,052 --> 00:13:58,120
WHO ARE YOU?

274
00:13:58,186 --> 00:14:00,822
I'M -- UH, D-DALLEN.

275
00:14:00,889 --> 00:14:04,693
REMEMBER?
UH, FROM CHURCH.

276
00:14:04,759 --> 00:14:07,562
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

277
00:14:07,629 --> 00:14:10,532
W-WE HAD SOME CLASSES,
UM, TOGETHER

278
00:14:10,599 --> 00:14:12,000
BACK IN JUNIOR HIGH.

279
00:14:12,067 --> 00:14:13,435
MS. SAWYER FOR SPANISH

280
00:14:13,502 --> 00:14:16,488
AND I THINK, UH, BUCKLEY
FOR SCIENCE.

281
00:14:16,555 --> 00:14:17,723
SO?

282
00:14:17,790 --> 00:14:21,493
UM, WELL, ACTUALLY I JUST WANTED
TO TALK TO EDDIE.

283
00:14:23,712 --> 00:14:26,581
W-WE'RE PLAYING
VOLLEYBALL TOMORROW,

284
00:14:26,681 --> 00:14:29,218
AND WE JUST WANTED TO KNOW
IF Y-YOU COULD COME.

285
00:14:29,284 --> 00:14:31,153
HE DOESN'T CARE.

286
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:33,455
ACTUALLY I JUST WANT-T-ED
TO TALK TO HIM.

287
00:14:33,522 --> 00:14:36,525
WELL, D-D-D-D-DALLEN,
WHAT ARE YOU -- STUPID?

288
00:14:36,591 --> 00:14:38,893
EDDIE'S NOT INTERESTED.
YEAH.

289
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:42,531
OH, AND, UH, JUST BECAUSE YOU
SAT NEXT TO ME YEARS AGO

290
00:14:42,598 --> 00:14:44,766
DOESN'T MEAN YOU SHOULDEVER
TALK TO ME AGAIN.

291
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:46,802
NO.
I J-JUST WANTED --

292
00:14:46,868 --> 00:14:49,371
I REMEMBER YOU.
EVERYONE CALLED YOU "TARD."

293
00:14:49,438 --> 00:14:50,805
YOU GOT MOVED TO SOME
RESOURCE CLASS

294
00:14:50,872 --> 00:14:51,873
'CAUSE OF YOUR S-STUTTER.

295
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:52,974
[ LAUGHTER ]

296
00:14:53,041 --> 00:14:55,610
NOW, GET OUTTA HERE!

297
00:15:01,216 --> 00:15:03,651
Man: NICE SHOT.
THERE IT IS. YEAH.

298
00:15:03,752 --> 00:15:06,321
YES. GOOD PLAY.

299
00:15:06,388 --> 00:15:08,991
OH!

300
00:15:09,057 --> 00:15:10,959
Man #2:
HERE YOU GO, SARA.

301
00:15:11,026 --> 00:15:12,594
YOUR SERVE.

302
00:15:12,660 --> 00:15:14,062
ALL RIGHT, LET'S DO IT.

303
00:15:18,634 --> 00:15:20,068
HEY! WATCH IT!

304
00:15:20,135 --> 00:15:21,136
GIVE ME THAT.

305
00:15:25,157 --> 00:15:26,124
Ashley: HEY!

306
00:15:26,191 --> 00:15:27,909
TRY PLAYING WITH THIS.

307
00:15:27,976 --> 00:15:29,243
COLTON!

308
00:15:29,361 --> 00:15:30,429
HERE, DUDE.

309
00:15:33,899 --> 00:15:37,403
AT LEAST EDDIE CAME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

310
00:15:41,707 --> 00:15:43,475
[ KNOCKS ON DOOR ]

311
00:15:43,542 --> 00:15:45,611
COLTON, WE WANT TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT YOUR FRIENDS.

312
00:15:45,677 --> 00:15:47,346
OH, GREAT.
IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

313
00:15:47,413 --> 00:15:48,514
HAVE YOU SEEN MY SHIRT?

314
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:49,748
WHAT SHIRT?

315
00:15:49,781 --> 00:15:52,217
THE WHITE ONE --
WITH THE NUMBERS.

316
00:15:52,283 --> 00:15:53,852
IN THE LAUNDRY ROOM.

317
00:15:57,055 --> 00:15:59,808
THERE'S NEVER A GOOD TIME
TO BRING IT UP, NOT WITH COLTON.

318
00:16:02,076 --> 00:16:03,728
WE GOT A CALL
FROM EDDIE'S MOM.

319
00:16:03,795 --> 00:16:06,965
I GOT COMPLAINTS FROM PARENTS
ABOUT SOMETHING YOU GUYS DID.

320
00:16:07,031 --> 00:16:10,002
WHY DO I CARE?
DID YOU INTERRUPT A GAME
AT CHURCH THE OTHER NIGHT?

321
00:16:10,069 --> 00:16:11,303
WE WERE JUST WALKING BY.

322
00:16:11,370 --> 00:16:13,672
STABBING A VOLLEYBALL
ISN'T JUST WALKING BY.

323
00:16:13,738 --> 00:16:14,939
WHATEVER.

324
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:17,009
COLTON, YOUHAVE
TO CLEAN UP YOUR ACT.

325
00:16:17,076 --> 00:16:18,377
THAT'S ORIGINAL.

326
00:16:18,444 --> 00:16:20,011
YOU DON'T SEEM TO CARE
ABOUT ANYTHING LATELY.

327
00:16:20,078 --> 00:16:21,012
NOT SCHOOL, YOUR FRIENDS.

328
00:16:21,079 --> 00:16:22,113
I LIKE MY FRIENDS.

329
00:16:22,180 --> 00:16:24,082
SO MUCH THAT YOU LIKE
TO GET THEM IN TROUBLE?

330
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:26,585
ARE YOU BLAMING ME?
THAT'S SUPPORTIVE.

331
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,987
THAT'S NOT BLAME.
IT'S RESPONSIBILITY.

332
00:16:29,054 --> 00:16:30,088
"RESPONSIBILITY."

333
00:16:30,155 --> 00:16:31,423
HOW ABOUT YOU WAIT A YEAR?

334
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:34,059
THEN WHEN I'M 18, I CAN 
BE RESPONSIBLE ALL ON MY OWN.

335
00:16:34,125 --> 00:16:35,827
DON'T TALK LIKE THAT.
WE'RE NOT PUSHING YOU OUT.

336
00:16:35,894 --> 00:16:36,995
WE JUST WANT WHAT'S BEST --

337
00:16:37,062 --> 00:16:39,130
BEST FOR ME?

338
00:16:39,197 --> 00:16:40,666
ARE WE DONE YET?

339
00:16:40,732 --> 00:16:41,900
[ SCOFFS ]

340
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:43,869
GOT TO RUN, MOM.

341
00:16:43,936 --> 00:16:45,803
I'DHATETO BE LATE
FOR SCHOOL.

342
00:16:48,807 --> 00:16:50,475
HEY, COACH.

343
00:16:50,542 --> 00:16:51,910
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

344
00:16:51,976 --> 00:16:53,245
YOU READY
FOR TOMORROW'S MATCH?

345
00:16:53,312 --> 00:16:55,046
YEAH.

346
00:16:55,113 --> 00:16:57,049
GOOD.

347
00:16:57,116 --> 00:16:59,218
YOU'RE THINKING
ABOUT CLAIRVILLE, AREN'T YOU?

348
00:16:59,284 --> 00:17:00,969
AM I THAT TRANSPARENT?

349
00:17:01,036 --> 00:17:02,270
.
LOOK,
STOP WORRYING ABOUT IT

350
00:17:02,337 --> 00:17:03,805
IT'S NOT TILL THE END
OF THE SEASON.

351
00:17:03,872 --> 00:17:05,590
I KNOW.

352
00:17:05,657 --> 00:17:07,325
YOU'RE GONNA PSYCHE YOURSELF OUT
AND MAKE IT WORSE.

353
00:17:07,392 --> 00:17:09,427
AND BY "IT,"
YOU MEAN MY GAME?

354
00:17:09,494 --> 00:17:10,996
NO, BY "IT,"
I MEAN YOUR PARANOIA.

355
00:17:11,063 --> 00:17:12,130
HEY.

356
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:13,465
LOOK, JUST PLAY YOUR BEST.

357
00:17:13,531 --> 00:17:15,300
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT'S AT STAKE.

358
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:17,169
EXCEPT IT DOES.

359
00:17:17,268 --> 00:17:20,038
I HEARD THAT.

360
00:17:20,105 --> 00:17:23,008
ALL RIGHT, LET'S WARM UP.

361
00:17:23,074 --> 00:17:24,642
THIS IS GONNA BE SWEET.

362
00:17:24,675 --> 00:17:27,178
DUDE, CHILL OUT.
IT'S JUST A PARTY.

363
00:17:27,278 --> 00:17:28,947
HEY, YOUR PARENTS
CALLED MINE.

364
00:17:29,014 --> 00:17:31,249
YEAH, THEY CORNERED ME
ABOUT THE OTHER DAY.

365
00:17:31,316 --> 00:17:33,118
YOU DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING,
DID YOU?

366
00:17:33,184 --> 00:17:34,920
WELL, YEAH.
THEY ASKED ME WHERE I WAS.

367
00:17:34,986 --> 00:17:36,521
LET'S GET THIS STRAIGHT
RIGHT NOW.

368
00:17:36,587 --> 00:17:39,457
YOU DON'T TELL THEM ANYTHING.
MAKE SOMETHING UP. LIE.

369
00:17:39,524 --> 00:17:40,892
I DON'T CARE.

370
00:17:40,959 --> 00:17:43,194
WHAT WE DO IS OUR BUSINESS,
NOT THEIRS.

371
00:17:43,294 --> 00:17:45,296
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

372
00:17:48,599 --> 00:17:49,801
[ BEEP ]

373
00:17:49,868 --> 00:17:52,037
HEY, BLAKE.
I'M ON MY WAY.

374
00:17:52,103 --> 00:17:53,438
YEAH, EDDIE'S WITH ME.

375
00:17:53,504 --> 00:17:54,439
[ BEEPING ]

376
00:17:54,505 --> 00:17:56,441
HEY, JUST A SECOND.

377
00:17:58,076 --> 00:18:00,578
IT WAS NOBODY.

378
00:18:00,645 --> 00:18:02,914
HEY, I'M GONNA BE THERE
IN FIVE MINUTES.

379
00:18:02,981 --> 00:18:04,315
DON'T START WITHOUT ME.

380
00:18:08,019 --> 00:18:10,655
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

381
00:18:10,721 --> 00:18:12,723
[ SIGHS ] YEAH?

382
00:18:12,824 --> 00:18:14,059
YOU'RE COMING TONIGHT,
RIGHT?

383
00:18:14,159 --> 00:18:15,059
TO WHAT?

384
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:16,795
E.
YOUR SISTER'S TENNIS GAM

385
00:18:16,861 --> 00:18:18,697
IT'S FRIDAY NIGHT.

386
00:18:18,763 --> 00:18:20,132
HERS IS THE FIRST GAME.

387
00:18:20,199 --> 00:18:22,234
YOU DON'T HAVE TO STAY
ALL NIGHT.
Mom, I already --

388
00:18:22,301 --> 00:18:24,836
Listen, you told Ashley
you'd be there.

389
00:18:24,903 --> 00:18:27,121
NOW, BE HOME IN 30 MINUTES.

390
00:18:27,188 --> 00:18:28,322
FINE. I'M COMING.

391
00:18:28,389 --> 00:18:29,390
Try not to be late.

392
00:18:29,457 --> 00:18:30,959
WHATEVER.

393
00:18:31,025 --> 00:18:31,960
[ BEEP ]

394
00:18:32,027 --> 00:18:33,528
[ SIGHS ]

395
00:18:37,265 --> 00:18:38,967
OH, I AM SORRY, HONEY.

396
00:18:39,034 --> 00:18:40,468
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

397
00:18:40,535 --> 00:18:43,571
KAREN IS SICK, AND THERE ISN'T
ANYBODY TO COVER THE DESK.

398
00:18:43,638 --> 00:18:44,872
MOM, I KNOW.
I GET IT.

399
00:18:44,973 --> 00:18:46,474
I REALLY WANTED
TO BE THERE.

400
00:18:46,541 --> 00:18:49,244
I KNOW.
I'LL BE FINE.

401
00:18:49,311 --> 00:18:50,812
GOOD LUCK.

402
00:18:54,015 --> 00:18:55,216
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

403
00:18:58,453 --> 00:19:00,121
COLTON?

404
00:19:02,690 --> 00:19:04,525
I DON'T KNOW
WHICH IS WORSE --

405
00:19:04,592 --> 00:19:06,294
IF HE WERE HERE
AND HE DIDN'T COME

406
00:19:06,361 --> 00:19:08,563
OR THAT HE'S NOT HERE
AT ALL.

407
00:19:26,731 --> 00:19:28,733
YOU READY?
YEP.

408
00:19:37,575 --> 00:19:40,945
I'M SORRY
FOR WHAT COLTON DID.

409
00:19:41,012 --> 00:19:43,315
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

410
00:19:43,381 --> 00:19:45,383
WHAT CAN WE DO ANYMORE?

411
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:48,119
I MEAN, HIS FRIENDS
ARE SUCH A BAD INFLUENCE.

412
00:19:48,185 --> 00:19:51,256
OR HE'S A BAD INFLUENCE
ON HIS FRIENDS.

413
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:54,259
GO!

414
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:57,695
WHOO!

415
00:19:57,762 --> 00:19:59,897
SOUNDS LIKE HE'S LOST SIGHT
OF WHAT'S RIGHT.

416
00:19:59,964 --> 00:20:02,334
IT'S BEEN MONTHS SINCE HE'S EVEN
BEEN TO CHURCH.

417
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:04,902
HE GETS SO CONFRONTATIONAL
WHEN WE EVEN BRING IT UP.

418
00:20:04,969 --> 00:20:07,472
HE EVEN MAKES FUN OF THE KIDS
THAT DO GO TO CHURCH.

419
00:20:07,539 --> 00:20:09,574
OH, HE'S JUST SO CONSUMED
WITH HIMSELF.

420
00:20:11,776 --> 00:20:13,911
WE'VE BEEN PRAYING FOR HIM.

421
00:20:13,978 --> 00:20:18,616
TRYING TO LISTEN, UNDERSTAND,
DISCIPLINE, ANYTHING.

422
00:20:18,683 --> 00:20:20,285
BUT HE JUST DOESN'T CARE.

423
00:20:20,352 --> 00:20:22,219
WE'D HOPED HE'D OUTGROW
THIS BEHAVIOR.

424
00:20:22,320 --> 00:20:25,222
INSTEAD,
IT'S JUST GOTTEN WORSE.

425
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:29,394
MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU CAN STILL DO.

426
00:20:29,461 --> 00:20:33,931
YOU'RE FAMILIAR WITH THE STORY
OF SAUL BEFORE HE BECAME PAUL.

427
00:20:33,998 --> 00:20:38,637
HE WAS PERSECUTING BELIEVERS
, THREATENING CHRIST'S CHURCH,

428
00:20:38,704 --> 00:20:41,807
UNTIL THE LORD INTERVENED.
DO YOU REMEMBER?

429
00:20:41,873 --> 00:20:43,274
YES.

430
00:20:43,341 --> 00:20:45,610
THE LORD CAME TO SAUL
AND CONFRONTED HIM.

431
00:20:45,677 --> 00:20:49,064
AND AFTER THAT,
SAUL CHANGED HIS WAYS.

432
00:20:49,131 --> 00:20:51,299
BUT HOW DOES THAT
RELATE TO US?

433
00:20:51,366 --> 00:20:52,700
THE LORD INTERVENED,

434
00:20:52,767 --> 00:20:55,303
BUT WE CAN ONLY DO SO MUCH
FOR COLTON.

435
00:20:55,370 --> 00:20:58,906
THAT'S TRUE.
COLTON MAKES HIS OWN DECISIONS.

436
00:20:58,973 --> 00:21:01,576
YOU CAN'T FORCE HIM
TO CHANGE.

437
00:21:01,643 --> 00:21:04,179
AND GOD
WON'T FORCE HIM, EITHER.

438
00:21:06,148 --> 00:21:09,651
YOU KNOW, THERE'S A VERSE IN
MATTHEW, I THINK, THAT CAN HELP.

439
00:21:12,687 --> 00:21:15,824
"COME UNTO ME,
ALL YE THAT ARE ARE HEAVY-LADEN,

440
00:21:15,890 --> 00:21:18,492
AND I WILL GIVE YOU REST."

441
00:21:18,593 --> 00:21:21,129
SO WE SHOULD COME TO HIM.

442
00:21:21,195 --> 00:21:23,481
PRAY THAT THE LORD
CAN TOUCH HIS HEART,

443
00:21:23,548 --> 00:21:26,818
SO COLTON WILL WANT
TO TURN TO THE LORD,

444
00:21:26,885 --> 00:21:28,453
SO HE'LL WANT TO CHANGE.

445
00:21:33,091 --> 00:21:35,494
HEY, EDDIE.
LET ME SEE YOUR CELLPHONE.

446
00:21:41,199 --> 00:21:43,468
[ SCREAMING ]

447
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:17,569
OUR FATHER IN HEAVEN, AS WE COME
BEFORE THEE THIS TIME.

448
00:22:21,939 --> 00:22:23,908
ENJOY.

449
00:22:23,975 --> 00:22:26,811
HEY, WE NEED MORE DRINKS,
AND, BLAKE, IT'S YOUR HOUSE.

450
00:22:26,878 --> 00:22:30,081
YOU'RE SO RIGHT.
COLTON. COLTON.

451
00:22:40,041 --> 00:22:41,775
GOOD GAME.
THANKS.

452
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:55,556
Hi, this is Jennifer.
Please leave a message.

453
00:22:55,623 --> 00:22:56,724
HEY, MOM.

454
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:58,226
UH, I KNOW
YOU'RE STILL WORKING,

455
00:22:58,292 --> 00:23:01,662
BUT I JUST WANTED TO LET YOU
KNOW THAT...I WON!

456
00:23:01,729 --> 00:23:04,498
COACH MILLER STILL THINKS
I HAVE A LITTLE BIT TO WORK ON

457
00:23:04,565 --> 00:23:06,267
BEFORE THE WHOLE
CLAIRVILLE THING.

458
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:08,636
ANYWAY, I WILL TALK TO YOU
WHEN I GET HOME,

459
00:23:08,702 --> 00:23:11,873
AND HAVE FUN AT WORK.
OKAY? BYE.

460
00:23:15,676 --> 00:23:16,978
WHOO!

461
00:23:17,045 --> 00:23:18,279
HA HA.

462
00:23:18,312 --> 00:23:20,949
MAN, BE CAREFUL.
WATCH YOUR DRIVING.

463
00:23:25,653 --> 00:23:27,588
UH, COLTON?

464
00:23:27,655 --> 00:23:29,257
YEAH?

465
00:23:32,026 --> 00:23:33,327
I NEED -- OHH.

466
00:23:33,427 --> 00:23:36,064
DUDE, WATCH THE ROAD, MAN.
WATCH THE ROAD.

467
00:23:36,130 --> 00:23:39,968
[ INSPIRATIONAL ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING ]

468
00:23:40,034 --> 00:23:42,937
YOU JUST TOOK THAT TURN
TOO FAST.

469
00:23:43,004 --> 00:23:45,073
YEAH.

470
00:23:49,310 --> 00:23:50,311
DUDE, WATCH THE ROAD!

471
00:23:50,344 --> 00:23:51,545
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

472
00:23:51,612 --> 00:23:52,697
BLAKE!

473
00:23:52,763 --> 00:23:54,265
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

474
00:23:54,332 --> 00:23:56,101
[ SIREN WAILS ]

