00:38:03,496 --> 00:38:07,700
WERE YOU REALLY TOLD TO STOP
WHAT YOU WERE DOING...

723
00:38:07,768 --> 00:38:10,703
WHEN YOU DIED, OR WHATEV
ER YOU WANT TO CALL IT?

724
00:38:10,771 --> 00:38:12,239
WAS THAT TRUE?

725
00:38:12,306 --> 00:38:14,658
YOU HEARD.

726
00:38:14,725 --> 00:38:16,944
YOUWERETALKING TO ME.

727
00:38:17,011 --> 00:38:19,279
[ Chuckling ]
WELL, YEAH, BUT...

728
00:38:22,049 --> 00:38:26,420
YEAH. IT'S TRUE.
OR AT LEAST I THINK IT IS.

729
00:38:26,486 --> 00:38:28,956
SO, WHY ARE YOU HERE NOW?

730
00:38:29,023 --> 00:38:32,192
I'M -- I'M NOT SURE
WHAT TO DO.

731
00:38:32,259 --> 00:38:36,063
AND -- AND I FEEL BAD

732
00:38:36,130 --> 00:38:37,965
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

733
00:38:38,032 --> 00:38:39,633
ESPECIALLY WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOU.

734
00:38:39,700 --> 00:38:43,204
SO, YOU'RE APOLOGIZING?

735
00:38:43,270 --> 00:38:45,439
UH, NO. YES.

736
00:38:45,506 --> 00:38:49,276
UM, I MEAN, I JUST --

737
00:38:49,343 --> 00:38:50,877
[ SIGHS ]

738
00:38:50,944 --> 00:38:55,582
IT'S NOT AS EASY
AS I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE.

739
00:38:55,682 --> 00:38:58,652
IT'S WEIRD NOW
WITH MY PARENTS...

740
00:38:58,719 --> 00:39:00,821
AND MY FRIENDS --

741
00:39:00,887 --> 00:39:02,289
THEY DON'T GET THIS?

742
00:39:02,356 --> 00:39:04,825
THEY WON'T TAKE IT
SERIOUSLY.

743
00:39:04,891 --> 00:39:07,861
THANK YOU...

744
00:39:07,928 --> 00:39:10,331
FOR YOUR APOLOGY.

745
00:39:10,397 --> 00:39:13,300
WHAT? REALLY?

746
00:39:13,367 --> 00:39:17,538
WOW. UM,
I DIDN'T EXPECT YOU TO --

747
00:39:17,604 --> 00:39:18,972
FORGIVE YOU?

748
00:39:19,039 --> 00:39:23,477
I'M NOT SURE I'M THERE YET,
BUT I KNOW YOU'RE NOT LYING,

749
00:39:23,544 --> 00:39:27,013
AND AT LEAST YOU'RE NOT
BEING A JERK.

750
00:39:29,349 --> 00:39:30,851
FEEL BETTER?

751
00:39:30,918 --> 00:39:32,186
YEAH.

752
00:39:32,253 --> 00:39:34,821
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE THAT'S
THE ONLY REASON I CAME OVER.

753
00:39:34,888 --> 00:39:36,573
I WOULDN'T WANT YOU
TO THINK THAT.

754
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:39,976
MAYBE YOU SHOULD MAKE IT RIGHT
WITH OTHER

755
00:39:40,009 --> 00:39:45,365
.
I MEAN, NO OFFENSE, BUT I'M SURE
I'M NOT THE ONLY ONE

756
00:40:02,199 --> 00:40:05,068
DALLEN.
HEY, DALLEN!

757
00:40:05,135 --> 00:40:06,136
WAIT UP.

758
00:40:06,203 --> 00:40:07,270
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

759
00:40:07,337 --> 00:40:09,472
I JUST WANTED TO SAY
I'M SORRY.

760
00:40:09,539 --> 00:40:10,741
DID I MISS SOMETHING?

761
00:40:10,808 --> 00:40:12,559
IS THE END
OF THE WORLD HERE?

762
00:40:12,626 --> 00:40:14,128
I'M SERIOUS.

763
00:40:14,194 --> 00:40:16,430
THE ONLY THING YOU'VE EVER
BEEN SERIOUS ABOUT

764
00:40:16,496 --> 00:40:18,365
IS MAKING EVERYBODY ELSE
MISERABLE.

765
00:40:21,468 --> 00:40:24,288
FINE. WHATEVER.
LET'S JUST GET THIS OVER WITH.

766
00:40:24,355 --> 00:40:26,857
HEY, I --
I MADE FUN OF YOU

767
00:40:26,923 --> 00:40:28,959
AND EMBARRASSED YOU IN FRONT
OF EVERYONE.

768
00:40:29,025 --> 00:40:30,827
GREAT APOLOGY.

769
00:40:30,894 --> 00:40:33,130
WELL, YOU WERE JUST
TRYING TO BE NICE.

770
00:40:33,197 --> 00:40:36,233
YOU DIDN'T DESERVE
WHAT I DID TO YOU.

771
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:37,567
I DON'T BUY IT.

772
00:40:37,667 --> 00:40:40,404
HEY, DALLEN, WAIT.

773
00:40:40,470 --> 00:40:41,671
I JUST WANTED TO SAY
I'M SORRY.

774
00:40:41,738 --> 00:40:44,274
DO YOU THINK SORRY
REALLY COVERS IT?

775
00:40:44,341 --> 00:40:47,076
WHAT ABOUT THE PEOPLE
YOU REALLY HURT, LIKE SARA?

776
00:40:47,177 --> 00:40:49,045
YOU KNOW, SHE WON'T BE ABLE
TO PLAY TENNIS

777
00:40:49,078 --> 00:40:50,564
FOR THE REST
OF THE SCHOOL YEAR.

778
00:40:50,631 --> 00:40:52,799
LIZ SAYS THAT'S JUST ENOUGH
TO MISS A CHANCE

779
00:40:52,866 --> 00:40:54,935
AT THIS ELITE TENNIS PROGRAM
THIS SUMMER.

780
00:40:55,002 --> 00:40:57,671
IT'S GONNA TAKE MORE.

781
00:40:57,737 --> 00:40:59,523
YOU CAN BE SORRY TODAY

782
00:40:59,589 --> 00:41:02,592
AND JUST BE BACK T-T-TO
TORMENTING EVERYONE TOMORROW.

783
00:41:08,933 --> 00:41:10,034
HEY, GUYS.

784
00:41:10,100 --> 00:41:11,435
WE'RE GETTING OUT OF HERE.
YOU COMING?

785
00:41:11,501 --> 00:41:12,436
I BETTER NOT.

786
00:41:12,502 --> 00:41:14,038
WHAT?
MY ARM.

787
00:41:14,104 --> 00:41:15,205
I'D JUST SLOW YOU DOWN.

788
00:41:15,272 --> 00:41:16,673
WHATEVER, DUDE.

789
00:41:16,740 --> 00:41:17,975
SURE.

790
00:41:18,042 --> 00:41:19,643
HEY, EDDIE.
WHAT'S UP?

791
00:41:19,709 --> 00:41:21,645
DO YOU THINK YOU SHOULD BE GOING
WITH THOSE GUYS?

792
00:41:21,711 --> 00:41:23,080
WHAT?

793
00:41:23,147 --> 00:41:25,115
BLAKE AND JOHN.
THEY CAN GET YOU IN TROUBLE.

794
00:41:25,182 --> 00:41:26,951
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
THEY'RE OUR FRIENDS.

795
00:41:27,017 --> 00:41:28,618
THEY'RE NOT
THE BEST FRIENDS.

796
00:41:28,685 --> 00:41:29,753
HOW CAN YOU SAY THAT?

797
00:41:29,819 --> 00:41:32,056
BECAUSE I KNEW WHAT A TERRIBLE
PERSON I WAS

798
00:41:32,122 --> 00:41:33,273
WHEN I WAS AROUND THEM.

799
00:41:33,340 --> 00:41:36,076
HEY, I'M PART OF THE GROUP.
I'M ACCEPTED.

800
00:41:36,143 --> 00:41:37,344
DO YOU GET THAT?

801
00:41:37,410 --> 00:41:38,812
I KNOW THAT'S
WHAT YOU WANTED,

802
00:41:38,879 --> 00:41:41,131
AND I KNOW I DRAGGED Y
OU INTO IT, BUT IT WAS STUPID.

803
00:41:41,197 --> 00:41:42,699
WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH YOU, DUDE?

804
00:41:42,766 --> 00:41:44,868
YOU STILL HAVE TIME
TO GET BETTER FRIENDS.

805
00:41:44,935 --> 00:41:47,804
SARA TAYLOR, OR DALLEN,
LIZ, ANYONE.

806
00:41:47,904 --> 00:41:49,573
I HAVE FRIENDS,
AND SO DO YOU.

807
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:51,307
AND TO SHOW YOU HOW GOOD
OF A FRIEND I AM,

808
00:41:51,375 --> 00:41:53,276
I'M GONNA FORGET YOU SAID
ANYTHING ABOUT THIS.

809
00:41:55,078 --> 00:41:56,529
MOM, WE'RE GONNA BE LATE.

810
00:41:56,562 --> 00:41:59,332
WE ARE NOT. I CAN GET US THERE
IN EIGHT MINUTES.

811
00:41:59,399 --> 00:42:01,567
ALIVE? I'D HATE TO GET TO
THE PHYSICAL THERAPIST OFFICE

812
00:42:01,668 --> 00:42:02,969
IN MORE PIECES
THAN LAST WEEK.

813
00:42:03,036 --> 00:42:04,070
HI, COLTON.

814
00:42:04,137 --> 00:42:06,640
OKAY, I'M GONNA GRAB MY PURSE
AND LOCK UP.

815
00:42:11,078 --> 00:42:12,812
I THINK I GOT WHAT YOU WERE
TALKING ABOUT.

816
00:42:12,929 --> 00:42:14,498
WHAT?

817
00:42:14,565 --> 00:42:16,833
IT'S NOT JUST
ABOUT APOLOGIZING.

818
00:42:16,900 --> 00:42:19,853
THOUGH THAT'S IMPORTANT,
YOU GOT TO DO MORE.

819
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:21,922
AND YOU GOT ALL THIS
FROM ME?

820
00:42:21,988 --> 00:42:24,658
WELL, YOU AND DALLEN AND...

821
00:42:24,725 --> 00:42:28,362
READING THE BIBLE.

822
00:42:28,429 --> 00:42:30,997
I HAVE TO MAKE AMENDS.

823
00:42:31,064 --> 00:42:33,066
OKAY.

824
00:42:33,133 --> 00:42:35,168
WHICH GOT ME THINKING
ABOUT YOU...

825
00:42:35,235 --> 00:42:36,469
COLTON.

826
00:42:36,536 --> 00:42:39,906
...AND I WANT TO HELP 
YOU GET BETTER.

827
00:42:39,973 --> 00:42:42,042
IS THIS YOUR PENANCE?

828
00:42:45,245 --> 00:42:47,047
THIS IS A REALLY
GOOD RACKET.

829
00:42:47,113 --> 00:42:48,181
,
YEAH, IT BETTER BE

830
00:42:48,248 --> 00:42:50,183
'CAUSE IF THAT SALES GUY
RIPPED ME OFF.

831
00:42:50,250 --> 00:42:52,052
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS.

832
00:42:52,119 --> 00:42:53,853
I WANT TO.

833
00:42:53,920 --> 00:42:55,955
I KNOW WE HAVEN'T BEEN
THE BEST OF FRIENDS,

834
00:42:55,988 --> 00:42:59,126
LT,
AND I KNOW
IT'S MOSTLY MY FAU

835
00:42:59,192 --> 00:43:02,562
BUT I DON'T WANT TO BE THE ONE
TO SPOIL YOUR DREAM.

836
00:43:02,629 --> 00:43:03,863
BUT HOW CAN YOU HELP?

837
00:43:03,930 --> 00:43:06,066
I MEAN,
YOU'RE NOT MUCH BETTER OFF.

838
00:43:06,133 --> 00:43:08,301
THIS WILL HEAL
IN A FEW WEEKS.

839
00:43:08,368 --> 00:43:10,370
DON'T FORGET,
I PLAY HOCKEY.

840
00:43:10,437 --> 00:43:12,572
THAT'S NOT EVEN CLOSE
TO TENNIS.

841
00:43:14,641 --> 00:43:17,810
YOU'RE SERIOUS,
AREN'T YOU?

842
00:43:17,911 --> 00:43:19,279
YEAH.

843
00:43:19,312 --> 00:43:20,313
ALL RIGHT.

844
00:43:20,413 --> 00:43:21,614
REALLY?

845
00:43:21,681 --> 00:43:23,216
YEAH. THERE'S SOME PEOPLE
COMING IN

846
00:43:23,283 --> 00:43:24,801
FROM THE CLAIRVILLE
TENNIS PROGRAM.

847
00:43:24,868 --> 00:43:27,070
YEAH, I HEARD ABOUT THAT.

848
00:43:27,170 --> 00:43:29,740
WELL, I WANT TO BE STRONG ENOUGH
FOR THEM WHEN THEY COME,

849
00:43:29,807 --> 00:43:34,094
AND RIGHT NOW, MY LEG'S
FEELING PRETTY USELESS.

850
00:43:34,161 --> 00:43:36,263
AT.
WELL, WE'LL WORK ON TH

851
00:43:36,329 --> 00:43:39,432
UH, HEY.

852
00:43:39,499 --> 00:43:42,802
THERE'S A YOUTH ACTIVITY
TOMORROW.

853
00:43:42,869 --> 00:43:44,071
OKAY.

854
00:43:44,138 --> 00:43:46,806
YOU SHOULD COME.
IT'LL BE FUN.

855
00:43:46,873 --> 00:43:50,810
I DON'T THINK ANYONE
WOULD WANT ME THERE.

856
00:43:50,877 --> 00:43:52,279
I DO.

857
00:43:52,346 --> 00:43:55,065
YOU READY, SARA?

858
00:43:56,700 --> 00:43:59,002
I GOT TO RUN.

859
00:43:59,069 --> 00:44:00,937
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

860
00:44:01,037 --> 00:44:02,038
GOT IT.

861
00:44:13,967 --> 00:44:16,202
YOU CAME.

862
00:44:16,269 --> 00:44:18,271
AND I'M WONDERING WHY.

863
00:44:18,338 --> 00:44:19,940
WE CAN'T EVEN PLAY.

864
00:44:20,006 --> 00:44:23,643
WELL, THAT'S NOT THE ONLY REASON
WHY I COME.

865
00:44:23,709 --> 00:44:25,311
WHY DO YOU COME THEN?

866
00:44:25,378 --> 00:44:27,047
TO BE WITH MY FRIENDS.

867
00:44:27,113 --> 00:44:29,983
YOU KNOW, THE PEOPLE
I CAN BE MYSELF AROUND.

868
00:44:30,050 --> 00:44:31,717
SO, WHAT, WE'RE JUST SUPPOSED
TO SIT HERE

869
00:44:31,818 --> 00:44:33,553
AND WATCH EVERYONE ELSE
HAVE A GOOD TIME?

870
00:44:33,619 --> 00:44:35,989
WELL, YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE RIGHT
IN THE MIDDLE OF EVERYTHING

871
00:44:36,056 --> 00:44:38,024
TO ENJOY IT, DO YOU?

872
00:44:38,091 --> 00:44:40,393
OKAY.

873
00:44:40,460 --> 00:44:43,329
GET IT, GET IT, GET IT.

874
00:44:43,396 --> 00:44:46,216
I'M NOT FEELING IT.

875
00:44:46,283 --> 00:44:48,852
IT'S LIKE A HOCKEY GAME.

876
00:44:48,919 --> 00:44:51,154
YOU CAN WATCH WITHOUT PLAYING
AND STILL LOVE IT.

877
00:44:51,254 --> 00:44:53,656
HOCKEY'S ABOUT WINNING.

878
00:44:53,724 --> 00:44:56,293
ALL THE ICE
AND THE ADRENALINE...

879
00:44:56,359 --> 00:44:57,895
AND THE WINNING.

880
00:44:57,961 --> 00:45:01,364
SO, WINNING
IS ALL THAT MATTERS?

881
00:45:01,431 --> 00:45:02,665
PEOPLE CHEERING YOU ON?

882
00:45:02,733 --> 00:45:05,068
GETTING CARRIED OFF
ON PEOPLE'S SHOULDERS?

883
00:45:05,135 --> 00:45:06,303
YEAH.

884
00:45:06,369 --> 00:45:08,271
NOT THIS SEASON.

885
00:45:08,338 --> 00:45:12,675
SORRY, BUT IT'S THE GLORY
YOU LIKE.

886
00:45:12,776 --> 00:45:15,678
SO?

887
00:45:15,779 --> 00:45:18,481
ALL RIGHT,
LET ME ASK YOU THIS.

888
00:45:18,548 --> 00:45:20,117
WHY IS IT
THAT WHEN YOU WIN,

889
00:45:20,183 --> 00:45:22,185
YOU GET CARRIED OFF
ON PEOPLE'S SHOULDERS,

890
00:45:22,285 --> 00:45:27,624
BUT WHEN YOU LOSE,
YOU BLAME YOUR TEAM?

891
00:45:27,690 --> 00:45:30,460
WHAT ABOUT YOU AND YOUR
GLORIFIED PING PONG?

892
00:45:30,527 --> 00:45:31,594
[ CHUCKLES ]

893
00:45:31,661 --> 00:45:33,696
TENNIS IS COMPLETELY
DIFFERENT.

894
00:45:33,797 --> 00:45:35,298
IT'S JUST ME
AND MY OPPONENT,

895
00:45:35,365 --> 00:45:37,801
AND I CAN'T BLAME ANYONE
FOR MY MISTAKES,

896
00:45:37,868 --> 00:45:41,171
AND WHEN I WIN,
I CAN BE PROUD OF MYSELF.

897
00:45:41,204 --> 00:45:42,705
SEE?

898
00:45:42,806 --> 00:45:46,193
WITHOUT GLOATING.

899
00:45:46,260 --> 00:45:49,146
[ BELL RINGS ]

900
00:45:50,914 --> 00:45:51,981
COLTON.
HEY, GUYS.

901
00:45:52,048 --> 00:45:53,082
HEY, NO SLING.

902
00:45:53,150 --> 00:45:54,718
YEAH. I JUST GOT BACK
FROM THE DOCTOR.

903
00:45:54,784 --> 00:45:55,919
LET'S GO CELEBRATE, MAN.

904
00:45:55,985 --> 00:45:57,554
I CAN'T.
I GOT TO GO TO CLASS.

905
00:45:57,587 --> 00:45:58,955
WHOA, WHOA.
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO CLASS.

906
00:45:59,022 --> 00:46:00,957
GUYS! STOP!

907
00:46:01,024 --> 00:46:02,292
ARE YOU FEELING
ALL RIGHT, MAN?

908
00:46:02,359 --> 00:46:04,761
I FEEL FINE.
I JUST CAN'T COME.

909
00:46:04,828 --> 00:46:06,796
YOU'VE BEEN SAYING THAT TO US
A LOT LATELY.

910
00:46:06,863 --> 00:46:08,097
SO?

911
00:46:08,165 --> 00:46:09,466
SO, ARE YOU EVEN
OUR FRIEND ANYMORE?

912
00:46:09,533 --> 00:46:10,467
OF COURSE I AM.

913
00:46:10,534 --> 00:46:11,735
SURE DOESN'T SEEM LIKE IT.

914
00:46:11,801 --> 00:46:13,920
YOU'VE GONE REALLY GOOD-BOY-LIKE
ON US, MAN.

915
00:46:13,987 --> 00:46:15,088
IS THAT A BAD THING?

916
00:46:15,154 --> 00:46:17,957
YOU WANT TO GO WITH THE REST
OF THEM?

917
00:46:20,860 --> 00:46:22,128
FINE.

918
00:46:22,195 --> 00:46:23,630
WHEN YOU SNAP OUT
OF THIS LITTLE HAZE

919
00:46:23,697 --> 00:46:25,364
YOU'RE GOING THROU
GH, COME FIND US.

920
00:46:25,432 --> 00:46:27,383
I'M GETTING OUT OF HERE.

921
00:46:40,480 --> 00:46:42,382
HEY, AMY.

922
00:46:42,449 --> 00:46:44,150
HEY.

923
00:46:44,216 --> 00:46:45,852
HEY, MIKE.

924
00:46:45,918 --> 00:46:47,420
HEY.

925
00:46:47,487 --> 00:46:48,988
YOU HERE TO START
WORKING AGAIN?

926
00:46:49,055 --> 00:46:50,823
NOT EXACTLY.

927
00:46:50,890 --> 00:46:53,125
I DIDN'T THINK
YOU'D WANT ME BACK.

928
00:46:53,192 --> 00:46:57,163
JUST, UH, THOUGHT YOU'D STOP BY
FOR OLD TIME'S SAKE?

929
00:46:59,699 --> 00:47:02,669
IT'S ABOUT $500.

930
00:47:02,735 --> 00:47:03,970
WHAT FOR?

931
00:47:04,036 --> 00:47:07,574
IT'S WHAT I OWE YOU,
PLUS INTEREST.

932
00:47:07,640 --> 00:47:11,611
UM, ABOUT ONCE A --
ONCE A SHIFT,

933
00:47:11,678 --> 00:47:14,180
I'D TAKE THE MONEY
AND POCKET IT.

934
00:47:14,246 --> 00:47:16,248
IT NEVER MADE IT
TO THE MACHINE.

935
00:47:16,316 --> 00:47:17,817
I STOLE IT.

936
00:47:17,884 --> 00:47:20,737
I HAD MY SUSPICIONS.

937
00:47:20,804 --> 00:47:24,641
AND I JUST WANTED
TO SAY THAT...

938
00:47:24,674 --> 00:47:26,175
I'M SORRY.

939
00:47:26,243 --> 00:47:28,678
I'M GLAD YOU TOLD ME
ABOUT THIS.

940
00:47:28,745 --> 00:47:32,582
WELL, THANKS FOR BEING COOL
ABOUT IT.

941
00:47:32,649 --> 00:47:34,251
I'LL SEE YOU AROUND.

942
00:47:51,434 --> 00:47:53,103
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

943
00:47:53,170 --> 00:47:56,773
UH, PRAYING.

944
00:47:56,839 --> 00:47:59,526
SORRY. I'VE NEVER SEEN YOU
KNEEL BEFORE.

945
00:47:59,593 --> 00:48:02,929
IT'S BETTER WHEN I KNEEL.

946
00:48:02,962 --> 00:48:05,899
HEY. ASHLEY.

947
00:48:05,965 --> 00:48:09,336
I -- I OWE YOU
SOME MONEY.

948
00:48:09,403 --> 00:48:10,787
WHY?

949
00:48:10,854 --> 00:48:14,925
BECAUSE I KIND OF TOOK IT
FROM YOUR ROOM.

950
00:48:14,991 --> 00:48:17,627
HOW DID YOU KNOW
WHERE I KEEP IT?

951
00:48:17,694 --> 00:48:20,964
IN THE JEWELRY BOX?
KIND OF OBVIOUS.

952
00:48:21,031 --> 00:48:22,232
COLTON.

953
00:48:22,298 --> 00:48:25,701
I'D PAY YOU BACK NOW,
BUT I'M KIND OF SHORT ON CASH.

954
00:48:25,802 --> 00:48:27,437
HOW DID I NOT NOTICE?

955
00:48:27,503 --> 00:48:29,472
I DON'T KNOW.
YOU KEEP A LOT IN THERE.

956
00:48:29,539 --> 00:48:31,908
YOU SHOULD THINK ABOUT GETTING
A BANK ACCOUNT.

957
00:48:31,975 --> 00:48:34,110
I WILL NOW.

958
00:48:34,177 --> 00:48:35,645
I'LL PAY YOU BACK.

959
00:48:35,711 --> 00:48:37,814
YOU BETTER.

960
00:48:37,881 --> 00:48:39,715
FINALLY.

961
00:48:39,783 --> 00:48:40,951
YOU KNOW, WHEN I WAS LITTLE

962
00:48:41,017 --> 00:48:42,786
I ALWAYS THOUGHT CRUTCHES
WERE SO COOL.

963
00:48:42,853 --> 00:48:45,288
ARE YOU GLAD YOU DON'T NEED
THEM ANYMORE?

964
00:48:45,355 --> 00:48:46,923
THIS IS WEIRD.

965
00:48:46,990 --> 00:48:47,991
WHAT?

966
00:48:48,058 --> 00:48:50,393
HAVE I ALWAYS BEEN
THIS PASTY?

967
00:48:50,460 --> 00:48:51,461
[ LAUGHS ]

968
00:48:51,527 --> 00:48:53,396
YOU KNOW, YOU NEED
TO TAKE IT EASY.

969
00:48:53,463 --> 00:48:56,299
I'M NOT THAT CRAZY ABOUT YOU
GETTING BACK INTO TENNIS YET.

970
00:48:56,366 --> 00:48:57,400
WHY NOT?

971
00:48:57,467 --> 00:48:59,753
DR. PEPPER SAID
THAT I CAN EASE INTO IT.

972
00:48:59,820 --> 00:49:02,889
NO, WHAT HE SAID IS YOU CAN BE
MORE ACTIVE OVERALL,

973
00:49:02,956 --> 00:49:04,858
AND YOUR KNEE
IS STILL SENSITIVE.

974
00:49:04,925 --> 00:49:06,026
WELL, DON'T WORRY.

975
00:49:06,092 --> 00:49:09,896
I MEAN, COLTON'S HELPING ME,
AND I WON'T OVERDO IT.

976
00:49:11,898 --> 00:49:14,768
SO, UM...

977
00:49:14,835 --> 00:49:19,339
DO YOU THINK COLTON WOULD HAVE
GOTTEN SO, NOT BAD, BUT...

978
00:49:19,405 --> 00:49:21,607
BAD?
YEAH.

979
00:49:21,674 --> 00:49:23,309
IF I HADN'T TOLD ON HIM --

980
00:49:23,376 --> 00:49:26,379
I MEAN, THAT'S WHEN HE STARTED
GETTING REALLY MEAN TO EVERYONE.

981
00:49:26,446 --> 00:49:31,451
I DON'T KNOW.
IT WAS HIS CHOICE EITHER WAY.

982
00:49:31,517 --> 00:49:33,219
YOU KNOW,
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

983
00:49:36,356 --> 00:49:39,676
WOW. HAVEN'T SEEN THIS
IN A WHILE.

984
00:49:39,743 --> 00:49:41,711
YEAH.

985
00:49:41,778 --> 00:49:43,630
FIGURED MY GRADES
COULDN'T GET MUCH WORSE.

986
00:49:43,697 --> 00:49:46,833
I'M GLAD YOU'RE AT LEAST
MAKING AN EFFORT NOW.

987
00:49:46,900 --> 00:49:48,802
YOU KNOW,
IF YOU EVER NEED ANYTHING,

988
00:49:48,868 --> 00:49:51,871
YOUR MOM AND I ARE HERE
FOR YOU.

989
00:49:51,938 --> 00:49:54,441
YEAH, I KNOW.

990
00:49:54,508 --> 00:49:58,044
YOU KNOW, I'VE NOTICED SOME
CHANGES IN YOU SINCE THE WRECK.

991
00:49:58,111 --> 00:49:59,813
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

992
00:50:05,084 --> 00:50:07,821
JOINING THE PANSY SPORT,
ARE WE, COLTON?

993
00:50:07,888 --> 00:50:10,740
AW, HOW NICE FOR SARA.

994
00:50:10,807 --> 00:50:11,974
SHUT UP, BLAKE.

995
00:50:12,042 --> 00:50:14,811
WHATEVER, MAN.

996
00:50:14,911 --> 00:50:16,079
YOU OKAY?

997
00:50:16,146 --> 00:50:19,315
I'M USED TO IGNORING THEM.
HOW ABOUT YOU?

998
00:50:19,382 --> 00:50:21,151
NEW DEVELOPMENT.

999
00:50:21,217 --> 00:50:24,487
THAT'S HARD.
I MEAN, THEY WERE YOUR FRIENDS.

1000
00:50:24,554 --> 00:50:25,655
THEY STILL ARE.

1001
00:50:25,721 --> 00:50:28,925
IT'S JUST THAT I DON'T LIKE
WHAT THEY DO ANYMORE.

1002
00:50:28,992 --> 00:50:31,261
IT'S PARTIALLY
MY FAULT, THOUGH.

1003
00:50:31,327 --> 00:50:32,828
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

1004
00:50:32,896 --> 00:50:35,298
COME ON, YOU KNOW
HOW I USED TO ACT.

1005
00:50:35,331 --> 00:50:37,667
YEAH, BUT THEY ACTED
THE SAME WAY.

1006
00:50:37,733 --> 00:50:41,071
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE YOU FORCED
THEM TO DO ANYTHING.

1007
00:50:41,137 --> 00:50:44,691
WELL, BLAKE AND JOHN, MAYBE,
BUT EDDIE.

1008
00:50:44,758 --> 00:50:46,392
OH.

1009
00:50:46,459 --> 00:50:49,528
YEAH, I JUST -- I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO GET THROUGH TO HIM.

1010
00:50:49,595 --> 00:50:52,365
WOW. I TOTALLY SOUND
LIKE MY PARENTS.

1011
00:50:52,431 --> 00:50:53,500
FRIGHTENING.
YEAH.

1012
00:50:53,567 --> 00:50:57,771
ANYWAY, I DON'T WANT EDDIE
TO BE LIKE ME.

1013
00:50:57,837 --> 00:50:59,205
CAN I ASK A FAVOR?

1014
00:50:59,289 --> 00:51:01,524
YEAH, SURE.

1015
00:51:01,591 --> 00:51:04,894
IF YOU HAVE ANY IDEAS
HOW TO HELP HIM,

1016
00:51:04,961 --> 00:51:07,497
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE
TO DO.

1017
00:51:07,564 --> 00:51:09,299
WELL, YEAH.

1018
00:51:09,366 --> 00:51:12,402
I DON'T KNOW ANY RIGHT NOW,
BUT I CAN THINK ABOUT IT.

1019
00:51:12,469 --> 00:51:13,570
THANKS.

1020
00:51:13,669 --> 00:51:16,239
NO PROBLEM.

1021
00:51:16,306 --> 00:51:17,307
MAYBE WITH BOTH OF US,

1022
00:51:17,373 --> 00:51:19,025
HE'LL SEE WE JUST
WANT TO BE HIS FRIEND.

1023
00:51:22,028 --> 00:51:24,097
SO, I THINK
COACH MILLER'S WORRIED

1024
00:51:24,163 --> 00:51:26,299
THAT I'M NOT GONNA BE READY
FOR CLAIRVILLE.

1025
00:51:26,399 --> 00:51:28,284
LET'S GET WORKING.

1026
00:51:30,319 --> 00:51:33,089
[ INTRO TO TOMMY DALTON'S
"DON'T LOOK DOWN" PLAYS ]

1027
00:51:39,963 --> 00:51:44,200
♪
♪ I WANT YOU TO KNOW THIS

1028
00:51:44,233 --> 00:51:48,838
♪ IF THE WORLD GOES AWAY ♪

1029
00:51:48,905 --> 00:51:53,476
♪♪ WE'D ALL JUST BE ANGELS ♪♪

1030
00:51:53,542 --> 00:51:57,546
♪ WITH NO ONE TO SAVE ♪

1031
00:51:57,613 --> 00:52:02,819
♪ AND I CAN'T LET THIS MOMENT ♪

1032
00:52:02,886 --> 00:52:07,056
♪ SLIP RIGHT THROUGH MY HANDS ♪

1033
00:52:07,123 --> 00:52:11,845
♪ JUST NEED YOU TO KNOW ME ♪

1034
00:52:11,911 --> 00:52:15,181
♪ THEN YOU'D UNDERSTAND ♪

1035
00:52:15,248 --> 00:52:16,616
HEY.

1036
00:52:16,683 --> 00:52:17,851
HEY.

1037
00:52:17,917 --> 00:52:19,252
WHAT ARE YOU READING?

1038
00:52:19,318 --> 00:52:20,486
FACTS.

1039
00:52:20,519 --> 00:52:22,689
♪ YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL,
IMPOSSIBLE ♪

1040
00:52:22,756 --> 00:52:25,224
♪ SO, WHY CAN'T I SAY? ♪

1041
00:52:25,291 --> 00:52:26,960
HEY, CUTIE.

1042
00:52:27,026 --> 00:52:29,328
[ LAUGHTER ]

1043
00:52:42,041 --> 00:52:43,976
GOOD JOB.

1044
00:52:44,043 --> 00:52:46,078
I HAVE A LOT OF WORK TO DO.

1045
00:52:46,145 --> 00:52:48,731
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
THAT WAS EXCELLENT.

1046
00:52:48,798 --> 00:52:50,500
HAVE YOU EVER
WATCHED TENNIS?

1047
00:52:51,718 --> 00:52:55,722
SO, HOW'S THE WHOLE
YOU-CHANGING THING GOING?

1048
00:52:55,788 --> 00:52:59,042
IT'S OKAY, I GUESS.
IT'S NOT VERY EASY.

1049
00:52:59,109 --> 00:53:01,411
IT'S

1050
00:53:01,477 --> 00:53:03,479
YEAH.

1051
00:53:03,579 --> 00:53:05,381
DO YOU FEEL BETTER?

1052
00:53:05,448 --> 00:53:07,250
A LITTLE.

1053
00:53:07,316 --> 00:53:09,318
AT LEAST I DON'T FEEL LIKE
EVERYONE HATES ME NOW.

1054
00:53:09,418 --> 00:53:12,338
EXCEPT FOR MAYBE JOHN,
BLAKE, AND EDDIE.

1055
00:53:12,405 --> 00:53:14,340
AND THEY MIGHT NOT
EVER GET WHY.

1056
00:53:14,407 --> 00:53:16,609
YEAH.

1057
00:53:16,675 --> 00:53:19,045
SO, WHAT WAS IT LIKE?

1058
00:53:19,112 --> 00:53:20,046
WHAT?

1059
00:53:20,113 --> 00:53:22,232
WHEN YOU DIED?

1060
00:53:22,299 --> 00:53:25,235
YOU SOUND LIKE MY SISTER.

1061
00:53:25,302 --> 00:53:28,838
.
WELL, NOT DYING,
BUT THE WHOLE VISION THING

1062
00:53:31,674 --> 00:53:34,611
IT WAS FRIGHTENING.

1063
00:53:34,677 --> 00:53:38,481
I JUST WANTED TO DIE...

1064
00:53:38,548 --> 00:53:41,451
OR HIDE FOREVER.

1065
00:53:41,518 --> 00:53:43,853
I KEPT HEARING WARNINGS.

1066
00:53:43,920 --> 00:53:48,925
IT WAS LIKE BEING TOLD
EVERYTHING I'VE EVER DONE WRONG.

1067
00:53:48,991 --> 00:53:52,995
NOT LIKE YOUR PARENTS
LECTURING YOU, BUT SERIOUS.

1068
00:53:55,498 --> 00:53:58,868
AND I REALIZED EVERYONE
WHO I'VE HURT.

1069
00:53:58,935 --> 00:54:01,704
MY PARENTS, ASHLEY, YOU,

1070
00:54:01,804 --> 00:54:06,309
ANYONE WHO I HAD
EVER BULLIED.

1071
00:54:06,376 --> 00:54:10,046
AND...I KNEW IN THE BACK
OF MY MIND

1072
00:54:10,112 --> 00:54:14,116
WHAT I SHOULD HAVE BEEN DOING
THE WHOLE TIME.

1073
00:54:14,183 --> 00:54:18,120
SO, WHEN I WOKE UP,
I KNEW WHAT I HAD TO DO.

1074
00:54:18,187 --> 00:54:21,240
YOU HAVE CHANGED, YOU KNOW?

1075
00:54:21,307 --> 00:54:24,977
YEAH.
I CAN FEEL IT.

1076
00:54:25,044 --> 00:54:30,516
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,
I LIKE IT -- THE NEW YOU.

1077
00:54:48,434 --> 00:54:50,803
Colton: DALLEN.

1078
00:54:50,870 --> 00:54:53,773
SARA. SARA.

1079
00:54:53,839 --> 00:54:56,109
RIGHT HERE.
RIGHT HERE.

1080
00:54:58,595 --> 00:55:01,030
I'LL GET IT.

1081
00:55:01,097 --> 00:55:02,364
NICE THROW.

1082
00:55:02,431 --> 00:55:04,300
I GUESS I HAVE TOO MUCH STRENGTH
IN MY ARM.

1083
00:55:04,366 --> 00:55:05,902
YEAH, THAT'S IT.

1084
00:55:05,968 --> 00:55:07,637
OKAY, SO MAYBE I'LL STICK
TO TENNIS THEN.

1085
00:55:07,704 --> 00:55:09,271
HEY, YOU'RE PRETTY GOOD
AT FRISBEE.

1086
00:55:09,338 --> 00:55:11,240
THANK YOU.
YEAH, RIGHT.

1087
00:55:11,307 --> 00:55:13,275
OH, HEY!

1088
00:55:13,342 --> 00:55:15,612
Ashley: JUST GIVE IT!

1089
00:55:15,678 --> 00:55:16,979
I DON'T HAVE IT.

1090
00:55:17,046 --> 00:55:17,963
GIVE IT BACK.

1091
00:55:18,030 --> 00:55:19,098
Colton: HEY.

1092
00:55:19,164 --> 00:55:20,433
YOU HAVING FUN, MAN?

1093
00:55:20,500 --> 00:55:22,268
WE WERE. YOU OKAY?

1094
00:55:22,335 --> 00:55:23,636
THEY WON'T GIVE
THE FRISBEE BACK.

1095
00:55:23,702 --> 00:55:25,471
[ Mockingly ] THEY WON'T GIVE
THE FRISBEE BACK.

1096
00:55:25,538 --> 00:55:26,705
MAN, CUT IT OUT!

1097
00:55:26,773 --> 00:55:27,841
YOU WANT THIS?
YEAH.

1098
00:55:27,907 --> 00:55:29,308
YEAH?

1099
00:55:29,375 --> 00:55:31,678
THEN GO GET IT.

1100
00:55:31,744 --> 00:55:33,379
I GUESS YOU GUYS
DON'T WANT TO PLAY.

1101
00:55:33,445 --> 00:55:34,780
OH, YOU'RE
INVITING US, NOW?

1102
00:55:34,847 --> 00:55:36,682
NO, WE'LL LEAVE THE CHURCHES
TO YOU, MAN.

1103
00:55:36,749 --> 00:55:39,318
HEY. EDDIE.

1104
00:55:41,454 --> 00:55:43,923
WHY DID THEY DO THAT?

1105
00:55:43,990 --> 00:55:47,660
OPPORTUNITY. THEY CAN TURN
ANY SITUATION INTO TROUBLE.

1106
00:55:47,726 --> 00:55:51,130
[ SIGHS ]
I'LL GET THE FRISBEE.

1107
00:55:51,197 --> 00:55:54,033
COME ON.
SHOW ME WHAT YOU GOT.

1108
00:55:56,536 --> 00:55:57,470
YOU'RE RUSTY.

1109
00:55:57,537 --> 00:55:59,138
THANKS.

1110
00:55:59,204 --> 00:56:00,824
COME ON,
LET'S TRY IT AGAIN.

1111
00:56:11,267 --> 00:56:13,869
HOW'S YOUR KNEE FEEL?

1112
00:56:13,936 --> 00:56:15,405
IT'S GOOD.

1113
00:56:15,471 --> 00:56:18,508
I'VE BEEN RUNNING AND GETTING
BACK INTO SHAPE.

1114
00:56:18,574 --> 00:56:19,742
YOU'RE FAVORING IT.

1115
00:56:19,809 --> 00:56:22,028
I KNOW.

1116
00:56:22,095 --> 00:56:24,230
ARE YOU REALLY READY
FOR A MATCH?

1117
00:56:24,297 --> 00:56:26,699
YEAH.

1118
00:56:31,503 --> 00:56:32,839
HEY, MOM.

1119
00:56:32,906 --> 00:56:36,109
WELL, WHO IS THIS YOUNG MAN
IN MY KITCHEN?

1120
00:56:36,175 --> 00:56:37,576
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

1121
00:56:37,643 --> 00:56:41,014
I JUST FINISHED TALKING
TO MR. COOPER.

1122
00:56:41,080 --> 00:56:42,215
OH?

1123
00:56:42,281 --> 00:56:45,018
HAD A DECENT AMOUNT
TO TALK TO HIM ABOUT --

1124
00:56:45,084 --> 00:56:47,153
THE STATUE
AND THE SPRAY PAINT

1125
00:56:47,220 --> 00:56:50,456
AND THE EVERYTHING ELSE.

1126
00:56:50,523 --> 00:56:52,091
HOW'D IT GO?

1127
00:56:52,158 --> 00:56:55,094
HE ALREADY KNEW, YOU KNOW,
ABOUT WHAT I DID.

1128
00:56:55,161 --> 00:56:58,297
BUT IT WAS GOOD.

1129
00:56:58,364 --> 00:57:00,433
I'M SO HAPPY FOR YOU.

1130
00:57:00,499 --> 00:57:02,785
YEAH.

1131
00:57:02,852 --> 00:57:05,388
YOU DON'T SEEM HAPPY.

1132
00:57:05,455 --> 00:57:06,522
I AM...

1133
00:57:06,589 --> 00:57:08,424
I GUESS.

1134
00:57:08,491 --> 00:57:10,126
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

1135
00:57:10,193 --> 00:57:13,662
IT'S JUST
IT STILL BOTHERS ME.

1136
00:57:13,729 --> 00:57:15,081
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

1137
00:57:15,148 --> 00:57:17,616
EVERYTHING I'VE DONE WRONG.

1138
00:57:17,683 --> 00:57:19,252
YOU STILL FEEL GUILTY?

1139
00:57:19,318 --> 00:57:22,155
YEAH.

1140
00:57:22,221 --> 00:57:24,974
DOES IT EVER GO AWAY?

1141
00:57:25,041 --> 00:57:28,745
SOMETIMES THE HARDEST THING
IS TO FORGIVE YOURSELF.

1142
00:57:28,811 --> 00:57:31,047
HOW DO YOU DO IT?

1143
00:57:31,113 --> 00:57:32,348
IT TAKES TIME.

1144
00:57:32,415 --> 00:57:35,784
IT'S HARD
TO COMPLETELY FORGET,

1145
00:57:35,885 --> 00:57:38,821
BUT ONE MORNING
YOU'LL WAKE UP,

1146
00:57:38,888 --> 00:57:43,159
AND AT LEAST THE MEMORY
WON'T HURT ANYMORE.

1147
00:57:43,226 --> 00:57:45,995
YOU GONNA BE OKAY?

1148
00:57:46,062 --> 00:57:49,131
YEAH.

1149
00:57:49,198 --> 00:57:51,100
THANKS.

1150
00:57:53,353 --> 00:57:55,154
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

1151
00:57:55,220 --> 00:57:56,589
WELL, WE'RE HEADED
THE SAME DIRECTION.

1152
00:57:56,656 --> 00:57:58,057
I THOUGHT MAYBE WE COULD
WALK TOGETHER.

1153
00:57:58,123 --> 00:57:59,124
WHATEVER.

1154
00:57:59,191 --> 00:58:00,526
ARE YOU IN A HURRY?

1155
00:58:00,593 --> 00:58:02,628
YOU GOT A PROBLEM
WITH THAT?

1156
00:58:02,695 --> 00:58:04,196
NO.

1157
00:58:04,229 --> 00:58:07,132
SO, UH, WE HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
AT CHURCH FOR A WHILE.

1158
00:58:07,199 --> 00:58:08,634
"WE"?

1159
00:58:08,701 --> 00:58:11,437
EVER NOTICE HOW IT'S ALWAYS
"WE" HAVEN'T SEEN YOU AT CHURCH?

1160
00:58:11,504 --> 00:58:14,907
IT'S A DEAD GIVEAWAY
THAT YOU'RE SENT TO "SAVE" ME.

1161
00:58:14,974 --> 00:58:16,542
OKAY.

1162
00:58:16,609 --> 00:58:18,644
IHAVEN'T SEEN YOU
IN A WHILE.

1163
00:58:18,711 --> 00:58:21,080
BUT IT DOESN'T LESSEN
THE FACT THAT WE --

1164
00:58:21,146 --> 00:58:22,882
I'DLIKE TO SEE YOU MORE.

1165
00:58:22,948 --> 00:58:24,350
ARE YOU HITTING ON ME?

1166
00:58:24,417 --> 00:58:25,385
WHAT?

1167
00:58:25,451 --> 00:58:27,186
SAVE IT FOR COLTON.

1168
00:58:27,252 --> 00:58:28,354
HEY!

1169
00:58:28,421 --> 00:58:30,255
LOOK, WE JUST --

1170
00:58:30,356 --> 00:58:33,559
I MEAN, COLTON AND I, WE JUST
WANT TO BE YOUR FRIEND.

1171
00:58:33,626 --> 00:58:35,895
DO YOU EVEN REALLY
KNOW COLTON?
WELL, YEAH.

1172
00:58:35,961 --> 00:58:37,597
'CAUSE HE'S NOT ALL CHURCHY
LIKE YOU THINK.

1173
00:58:37,663 --> 00:58:40,132
HE PROBABLY DOESN'T EVEN CARE
ABOUT YOU.

1174
00:58:40,199 --> 00:58:41,367
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

1175
00:58:41,434 --> 00:58:43,903
I'VE SEEN HIM GET ALL CHURCHY
ON GIRLS BEFORE.

1176
00:58:43,969 --> 00:58:45,270
IT'S AN ACT.

1177
00:58:45,338 --> 00:58:47,172
10 MINUTES LATER
HE'S MAKING OUT WITH THEM.

1178
00:58:47,239 --> 00:58:48,674
NEXT DAY HE DOESN'T
EVEN SAY HI.

1179
00:58:48,741 --> 00:58:49,842
HE'S NOT LIKE THAT ANYMORE,

1180
00:58:49,909 --> 00:58:51,711
AND YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE
LIKE THAT EITHER.

1181
00:58:51,777 --> 00:58:53,379
SAVE IT.

1182
00:58:53,446 --> 00:58:55,765
ARE YOU EVEN HAPPY
WITH WHO YOU ARE?

1183
00:59:08,561 --> 00:59:10,396
ARE YOU TRYING
TO MAKE ME FEEL BETTER?

1184
00:59:10,463 --> 00:59:12,665
NOT BY MAKING A FOOL
OF MYSELF.

1185
00:59:12,732 --> 00:59:15,785
YOU KNOW, WE NEED TO DO
SOMETHINGI'MGOOD AT.

1186
00:59:15,852 --> 00:59:18,554
ARE YOU FEELING
A LITTLE HUMBLED?

1187
00:59:18,620 --> 00:59:20,923
EMBARRASSED.
THERE'S A DIFFERENCE.

1188
00:59:20,990 --> 00:59:24,961
ALL RIGHT. WELL,
WHAT DID YOU HAVE IN MIND?

1189
00:59:27,429 --> 00:59:30,166
I, UH, TAKE IT
YOU MISS THIS.

1190
00:59:30,232 --> 00:59:33,903
WHY WOULDN'T I?
COME ON.

1191
00:59:33,970 --> 00:59:35,371
[ LAUGHS ]

1192
00:59:35,437 --> 00:59:38,440
YOU KNOW, I THINK YOU'D FEEL
MORE COMFORTABLE IN THESE.

1193
00:59:38,507 --> 00:59:40,742
BUT THE BLADE'S SHORTER.
SO?

1194
00:59:40,810 --> 00:59:42,311
WELL, I ALWAYS
KIND OF FIGURED

1195
00:59:42,378 --> 00:59:45,214
THAT A LONGER BLADE WOULD,
YOU KNOW, HELP ME -- WHOA!

1196
00:59:45,247 --> 00:59:47,884
KEEP MY BALANCE.

